{"id":822,"date":"2021-04-03T16:08:51","date_gmt":"2021-04-03T14:08:51","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.gotriple.eu\/?page_id=822"},"modified":"2021-04-05T17:30:23","modified_gmt":"2021-04-05T15:30:23","slug":"privacy-policy-for-triple-thatcamps","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/privacy-policy-for-triple-thatcamps\/","title":{"rendered":"Data Privacy Statement for TRIPLE ThatCamps"},"content":{"rendered":"<div id=\"modal-ready\">\n<p>When registering for the event <a href=\"https:\/\/survey3.gwdg.de\/index.php?r=survey\/index&amp;sid=349761&amp;newtest=Y&amp;lang=en\">TRIPLE ThatCamp #1<\/a>, you agree to the statements below related to personal data collected in this context. Personal data are all data that can be related to you personally, such as your name, address, email address, your behaviour as user.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator is-style-default\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h5><strong>Event registration<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>If you enter information in the input fields provided and submit the form, the following data will be transmitted, stored and processed electronically by staff of Max Weber Foundation (TRIPLE project):<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>First name<\/li><li>Last name<\/li><li>Email address&nbsp;<\/li><li>Your primary institutional affiliation (optional)<\/li><li>Organization\/Institution (optional)<\/li><li>Country of residence (optional)<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The personal data that you voluntarily provide by submitting the form will be used for the following purposes:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Confirmation of registration<\/li><li>Creation of participant lists<\/li><li>Provision of information about the event<\/li><li>Event evaluation<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The legal basis is Art. 6 para. 1 lit. f GDPR.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Storage period<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your personal data will be stored for as long as it is required to achieve the stated purposes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Transmission to third countries<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There is no transfer of data to third countries.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Non-provision<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The data is required for your registration for and your participation in our event. Failure to provide it will result in you not being able to attend the event.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Your rights<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) gives you the following rights regarding the processing of your personal data:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>right to withdrawal of consent (Art. 7 (3) GDPR)<\/li><li>right of access (Art. 15 GDPR)<\/li><li>right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)<\/li><li>right to erasure or &#8220;right to be forgotten&#8221; (Art. 17 GDPR)<\/li><li>right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)<\/li><li>obligation to notify (Art. 19 GDPR)<\/li><li>right to data portability (Art. 20 GDPR)<\/li><li>right to object (Art. 21 GDPR).<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>You also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority (Art. 77 GDPR) if you consider that the processing of your personal data is carried out unlawfully.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To exercise your above rights, please contact us by mail or email at:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Dr. Stefanie Pohle<br>Max Weber Foundation<br>Rheinallee 6<br>53173 Bonn<br>Email: <a href=\"mailto:triple@operas-eu.org\">triple@operas-eu.org<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator is-style-default\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h5><strong>Documentation of the event<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>We will document the event by saving and storing materials and chat contributions created by the participants, and take screenshots of the video conference. If you do not want your name to appear on these documents, we recommend using initials or a pseudonym instead of your full real name as personal identifier in the tools listed below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Materials created by the participants<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For documentation purposes, we will capture and store materials created collaboratively by the participants on the Miro board (see below) in the course of the event. After the event, we may upload these materials onto the repository <a href=\"https:\/\/zenodo.org\/\">Zenodo<\/a>, use them in academic and non-academic publications and\/or use them for communication purposes, i.e. publish them on the TRIPLE project\u2019s website and social media channels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Chats<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If chat functions in Zoom and\/or Miro are used, your text inputs will be processed and saved for documentation purposes, if applicable, until they are deleted manually.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Screenshots<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We will take screenshots of the Zoom video conference (see below) during the event. They will be stored and used for communication purposes, i.e. published on the TRIPLE project\u2019s website and distributed via social media channels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator is-style-default\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h5><strong>Responsible body: Contact details<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Responsible body<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Responsible according to Art. 4 (7) of the EU General Data Protection Regulation is the TRIPLE partner<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Max Weber Foundation (MWS)<br>Rheinallee 6<br>53173 Bonn<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><strong>Data protection officer<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Reinhard Hi\u00df<br>Max Weber Foundation<br>Rheinallee 6<br>53173 Bonn<br>Email: <a href=\"mailto:datenschutz@maxweberstiftung.de\">datenschutz@maxweberstiftung.de<\/a>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator is-style-default\"\/>\n\n\n\n<h5><strong>Third-party applications<\/strong><\/h5>\n\n\n\n<p>The event activities will include the use of third-party applications that process personal data. It is explicitly pointed out that the third-party tools used are subject solely to their respective cookie and privacy policies. The event organisers have no influence on the privacy settings of these services. By participating in the event you agree to their privacy policies. Please contact the providers directly if you wish to receive more information or if you wish to assert your rights.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Video conferencing<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This event will use video conferencing services through <a href=\"https:\/\/zoom.us\/\">Zoom<\/a>. A registration for a Zoom account is not necessary for using the tool during the event.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Privacy statement: <a href=\"https:\/\/zoom.us\/privacy\">https:\/\/zoom.us\/privacy<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Contact: Lionheart Squared Ltd, Attention: Data Privacy, 2 Pembroke House, Upper Pembroke Street 28-32, Dublin, DO2 EK84, Republic of lreland, <a href=\"mailto:zoom@LionheartSquared.eu\">zoom@LionheartSquared.eu<\/a>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Zoom account for the TRIPLE ThatCamp is being provided and managed by TRIPLE project partner <a href=\"https:\/\/www.huma-num.fr\/\">Huma-Num<\/a>. Contact person: Emilie Bloti\u00e8re (<a href=\"mailto:emilie.blotiere@huma-num.fr\">emilie.blotiere@huma-num.fr<\/a>).&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>Collaborative work<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/miro.com\">Miro<\/a> enables collaborative work on a virtual whiteboard. A registration for a Miro account is not necessary for using the tool during the event.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Privacy statement: <a href=\"https:\/\/miro.com\/legal\/privacy-policy\/\">https:\/\/miro.com\/legal\/privacy-policy\/<\/a>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Contact: RealtimeBoard Inc. dba Miro, 201 Spear Street, Suite 1100, San Francisco, CA 94105, USA, <a href=\"mailto:privacy@miro.com\">privacy@miro.com<\/a>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Miro account for the TRIPLE ThatCamp is being provided and managed by TRIPLE project partner <a href=\"https:\/\/www.know-center.tugraz.at\/\">Know-Center<\/a>. Contact person: Gert Breitfuss (<a href=\"mailto:gbreitfuss@know-center.at\">gbreitfuss@know-center.at<\/a>).&nbsp;<\/p>\n<\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>When registering for the event TRIPLE ThatCamp #1, you agree to the statements below related to personal data collected in this context. Personal data are all data that can be related to you personally, such as your name, address, email<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/822"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=822"}],"version-history":[{"count":5,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/822\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":830,"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/822\/revisions\/830"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/project.gotriple.eu\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=822"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}